---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout title="Privacy Policy - Radu Georoceanu" description="Privacy policy for radugeo.com in accordance with GDPR.">
  <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-text-primary">Privacy Policy</h1>

  <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mb-8">Last updated: January 2025</p>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-text-primary">1. Data Controller</h2>
    <div class="text-text-secondary space-y-1">
      <p>Radu Georoceanu</p>
      <p>Friedenstr. 2</p>
      <p>85609 Aschheim, Germany</p>
      <p>Email: contact@radugeo.com</p>
      <p>Phone: +49 176 588 30284</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-text-primary">2. Overview of Data Processing</h2>
    <p class="text-text-secondary">
      We take the protection of your personal data very seriously. We treat your personal data confidentially and in accordance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), the German Federal Data Protection Act (BDSG), and other applicable data protection regulations.
    </p>
    <p class="text-text-secondary mt-2">
      When you use this website, various personal data is collected. This privacy policy explains what data we collect and what we use it for.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-text-primary">3. Hosting</h2>
    <p class="text-text-secondary">
      This website is hosted on GitHub Pages, a service provided by GitHub, Inc., 88 Colin P Kelly Jr St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA. When you visit this website, GitHub may collect server log files including your IP address, browser type, operating system, referrer URL, time of access, and pages visited.
    </p>
    <p class="text-text-secondary mt-2">
      For more information, see the
      <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light">GitHub Privacy Statement</a>.
    </p>
    <p class="text-text-secondary mt-2">
      The use of GitHub Pages is based on Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR. We have a legitimate interest in a reliable presentation of our website.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-text-primary">4. Google Analytics</h2>
    <p class="text-text-secondary">
      This website uses Google Analytics, a web analytics service provided by Google Ireland Limited, Gordon House, Barrow Street, Dublin 4, Ireland ("Google").
    </p>
    <p class="text-text-secondary mt-2">
      Google Analytics uses cookies that enable an analysis of your use of the website. The information generated by the cookie about your use of this website is usually transmitted to a Google server in the USA and stored there. We use Google Analytics with IP anonymization enabled. This means your IP address is truncated within the EU/EEA before transmission.
    </p>
    <p class="text-text-secondary mt-2">
      The use of Google Analytics is based on Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR (consent). Google Analytics is only activated after you have given your explicit consent via the cookie consent banner. You can withdraw your consent at any time by clicking "Cookie Settings" in the footer of our website.
    </p>
    <p class="text-text-secondary mt-2">
      You can also prevent the collection of your data by Google Analytics by using the
      <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-text-primary">5. Google Fonts</h2>
    <p class="text-text-secondary">
      This website uses web fonts provided by Google (Google Fonts). When you open a page, your browser loads the required fonts from Google servers. This is necessary for the correct display of the website. Your browser establishes a connection to Google servers, through which Google learns that this website was accessed via your IP address.
    </p>
    <p class="text-text-secondary mt-2">
      The use of Google Fonts is based on Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR. We have a legitimate interest in the uniform presentation of the typeface on our website.
    </p>
    <p class="text-text-secondary mt-2">
      For more information, see the
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light">Google Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-text-primary">6. Google Calendar</h2>
    <p class="text-text-secondary">
      We use Google Calendar for appointment booking. When you click the "Book a Call" link, you are redirected to Google Calendar, which is operated by Google Ireland Limited. Google's privacy policy applies to the use of this service.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-text-primary">7. Cookies</h2>
    <p class="text-text-secondary">
      This website uses cookies. Cookies are small text files stored on your device by your browser. Some cookies are technically necessary for the website to function ("essential cookies"), while others are used for analytics purposes.
    </p>
    <p class="text-text-secondary mt-2">
      <strong class="text-text-primary">Essential data:</strong> We store a language preference in your browser's local storage to remember your language selection. This is technically necessary and does not require consent.
    </p>
    <p class="text-text-secondary mt-2">
      <strong class="text-text-primary">Analytics cookies:</strong> Google Analytics sets cookies to analyze website usage. These cookies are only set after you have given your explicit consent. See section 4 for details.
    </p>
    <p class="text-text-secondary mt-2">
      <strong class="text-text-primary">Cookie consent:</strong> When you first visit our website, a cookie consent banner is displayed. Your choice (accept or reject) is stored in your browser's local storage. You can change your consent at any time by clicking "Cookie Settings" in the footer. If you reject cookies or withdraw your consent, all analytics cookies are deleted and no further analytics data is collected.
    </p>
    <p class="text-text-secondary mt-2">
      You can also configure your browser to inform you about the setting of cookies, allow cookies only in individual cases, exclude the acceptance of cookies for certain cases or in general, and activate the automatic deletion of cookies when closing the browser.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-text-primary">8. Your Rights</h2>
    <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">
      Under the GDPR, you have the following rights regarding your personal data:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-text-secondary space-y-2">
      <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Right of access</strong> (Art. 15 GDPR) — You can request information about your personal data we process.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Right to rectification</strong> (Art. 16 GDPR) — You can request correction of inaccurate personal data.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Right to erasure</strong> (Art. 17 GDPR) — You can request deletion of your personal data.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Right to restriction of processing</strong> (Art. 18 GDPR) — You can request restriction of processing of your data.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Right to data portability</strong> (Art. 20 GDPR) — You can request to receive your data in a structured, commonly used format.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Right to object</strong> (Art. 21 GDPR) — You can object to the processing of your personal data at any time.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-text-secondary mt-4">
      To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at <a href="mailto:contact@radugeo.com" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light">contact@radugeo.com</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-text-primary">9. Right to Complain</h2>
    <p class="text-text-secondary">
      You have the right to lodge a complaint with a data protection supervisory authority (Art. 77 GDPR). The competent supervisory authority is:
    </p>
    <div class="text-text-secondary mt-2 space-y-1">
      <p>Bayerisches Landesamt für Datenschutzaufsicht (BayLDA)</p>
      <p>Promenade 18, 91522 Ansbach, Germany</p>
      <p>
        <a href="https://www.lda.bayern.de" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light">www.lda.bayern.de</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</LegalLayout>
